27:32.300 --> 27:35.292
The more Peter's old allies
appear in lockstep against him,

27:35.340 --> 27:37.558
the more it keeps
a spotlight on him.

27:37.610 --> 27:40.955
It deflects culpability
from our guys.

27:41.000 --> 27:43.264
I call it
"the coalition of the innocent."

27:43.310 --> 27:47.041
This isn't a good idea.

27:47.100 --> 27:48.226
Okay.

27:48.270 --> 27:49.658
Then let's go.

27:49.710 --> 27:50.654
I can't.

27:50.710 --> 27:53.224
I just want to talk.

27:53.280 --> 27:54.668
Tomorrow.
No.

27:54.710 --> 27:55.836
Tonight.

27:55.890 --> 27:58.791
Oh.

27:58.850 --> 28:00.977
Thank you.
Yeah.

28:03.500 --> 28:05.809
I didn't handle
that well earlier,

28:05.850 --> 28:09.638
and then I came back
here and it was awkward,

28:09.680 --> 28:12.331
and I know that if you have
two awkward moments in a row,

28:12.380 --> 28:15.247
that it can be
trouble clawing it back.

28:15.300 --> 28:18.428
What are we clawing back?

28:18.470 --> 28:19.869
That thing that I gave you...

28:19.910 --> 28:20.865
The Mars property?

28:20.910 --> 28:24.732
Yeah.

28:24.790 --> 28:26.735
See, I didn't know
that I was coming here

28:26.790 --> 28:28.746
and we were gonna have
a serious conversation.

28:28.790 --> 28:30.348
It was...

28:30.400 --> 28:33.654
it was in my pocket, and it was
just supposed to be this...

28:33.710 --> 28:36.133
this fun thing.

28:36.190 --> 28:38.829
I like space,
I like stuff about space.

28:38.890 --> 28:41.927
I get it.

28:41.980 --> 28:42.924
I'm fine.

28:42.980 --> 28:43.924
I'd better get back.

28:43.980 --> 28:46.323
No, please wait.

28:47.330 --> 28:49.764
Uh...

28:49.810 --> 28:53.155
I don't like spending more
than a year in any one place,

28:53.200 --> 28:55.725
I like to be able to drop
everything at a moment's notice

28:55.770 --> 28:56.759
and just go.

28:56.820 --> 28:58.594
Then go, no one's stopping you.

28:58.640 --> 28:59.686
You are.

28:59.730 --> 29:00.776
No, I'm not.

29:00.820 --> 29:04.085
Yes, you are.

29:04.130 --> 29:06.860
[car horns honking]

29:06.910 --> 29:09.083
Okay.

29:09.130 --> 29:11.655
I think we need to clarify
what we're saying here.

29:11.700 --> 29:15.045
I want you, too.

29:19.010 --> 29:19.965
You do?

29:20.010 --> 29:22.797
I do,

29:22.840 --> 29:26.583
but I am trying to explain
to you that I can't be...

29:26.630 --> 29:28.450
stuck.

29:28.500 --> 29:31.674
And I would make you feel stuck?

29:31.720 --> 29:33.199
No.

29:33.240 --> 29:35.629
No, you just have
this whole life here.

29:35.680 --> 29:39.207
You have beautiful kids,
a beautiful place,

29:39.250 --> 29:40.296
and a business.

29:40.340 --> 29:42.900
And you want me to give that up?No.

29:42.950 --> 29:44.724
No, I am just...
I'm bringing up a problem.

29:44.780 --> 29:46.907
I'm not saying
that there's a solution.

29:46.950 --> 29:48.212
Okay.

29:48.260 --> 29:52.082
I'm gonna repeat to you
what I thinkI heard.

29:52.130 --> 29:56.692
You want to go somewhere else
and you want me to go with you,

29:56.750 --> 29:58.308
but not now,
but at some point

29:58.360 --> 30:00.828
when you get itchy
about staying in one place?

30:03.270 --> 30:07.092
[chuckles]

30:07.150 --> 30:09.368
Oth”

30:09.410 --> 30:10.718
I need to think on this.

30:33.260 --> 30:35.728
[indistinct conversations]

30:35.790 --> 30:37.781
So, do you know anyone here?

30:37.830 --> 30:38.785
A few.

30:38.830 --> 30:40.957
So why law school?

30:41.010 --> 30:42.432
I thought you'd be happy.

30:42.490 --> 30:43.445
I don't know.

30:43.490 --> 30:44.787
Feels like a trick.

30:44.840 --> 30:45.829
The law is exciting.

30:45.880 --> 30:46.835
Things move fast.

30:46.880 --> 30:49.189
Uh, no, they don't.

30:49.230 --> 30:50.834
Most of the law
is just boring...

30:50.890 --> 30:52.573
paperwork and meetings.[phone rings]

30:52.630 --> 30:54.188
Hello?

30:54.240 --> 30:55.662
How rude.

30:55.720 --> 30:57.415
Answering your cell
at a dinner party?

30:57.460 --> 31:00.020
Oh, hi. Um, yeah, I'm standing
right next to him. Why?

31:00.070 --> 31:01.116
Who is it?

31:01.160 --> 31:02.889
Mike Tascioni.

31:02.940 --> 31:03.850
Tom is sick.

31:03.900 --> 31:05.549
Why's he calling you?

31:05.600 --> 31:07.295
And why's he calling you
about his dog?

31:07.340 --> 31:08.329
We've grown close.

31:08.380 --> 31:09.722
He couldn't get a hold of you.

31:09.780 --> 31:11.554
What number is he trying?
Shh!

31:11.600 --> 31:14.342
Oh, no, that-that's
terrible.

31:14.390 --> 31:16.426
Uh... okay, hold on.

31:16.480 --> 31:19.517
Tom had a nervous reaction
to medication.

31:19.570 --> 31:21.219
And he can't argue in court.

31:21.270 --> 31:22.919
What?

31:22.960 --> 31:24.564
Mike, what?

31:24.620 --> 31:26.918
You can't just...

31:26.970 --> 31:28.961
You're leaving us in the lurch?

31:29.010 --> 31:30.659
I don't care
how sick your dog...

31:30.710 --> 31:32.792
He hung up on me.

31:32.840 --> 31:34.489
Eli, can I borrow you?

31:34.540 --> 31:36.974
I-I'm kind of in the middle of
an emergency right now, Diane.

31:37.020 --> 31:39.068
Listen, can Cary Agos hurt you

31:39.110 --> 31:41.931
with this
Richard Locke business?

31:41.980 --> 31:43.288
I just lost
Peter's trial lawyer.

31:43.330 --> 31:44.581
I need your help.

31:44.640 --> 31:45.982
See?
Things do move fast.

31:53.120 --> 31:54.815
Why did you veto
the blood spatter?

31:54.860 --> 31:56.168
What?

31:56.210 --> 31:57.859
The blood spatter at the
Richard Locke crime scene.

31:57.910 --> 32:00.902
It pointed to his guilt and you
told the lab tech not to use it.

32:00.960 --> 32:04.339
Did you hire a new investigator?

32:04.400 --> 32:06.265
Or is this from Jason Crouse?

32:06.310 --> 32:07.652
Answer the question, Peter.

32:07.700 --> 32:09.964
Why did you veto
the blood spatter?

32:10.010 --> 32:11.352
The blood spatter
was compromised

32:11.400 --> 32:13.960
by the lab tech
who collected it.

32:14.010 --> 32:15.705
I was there, I saw it.

32:15.750 --> 32:20.847
So, all of a sudden you decide
to show up at a crime scene?

32:20.890 --> 32:22.494
What the hell were you thinking?

32:22.540 --> 32:27.284
Listen, Eli, this case was going
to be scrutinized.

32:27.330 --> 32:28.979
It was going to be our O.J.,

32:29.030 --> 32:30.895
so I went down there
to get ahead of it.

32:30.940 --> 32:33.898
Except this lab tech walked
right through the blood.

32:33.950 --> 32:36.726
So I vetoed it.

32:36.780 --> 32:38.725
Because allowing it
would've lost us the trial.

32:38.780 --> 32:39.940
And the bullets?

32:40.000 --> 32:41.900
You were the last person
to sign for them.

32:41.960 --> 32:44.690
Yeah, like I said, this blood
spatter was a royal screwup.

32:44.740 --> 32:46.219
So I went down to
look into this lab tech,

32:46.260 --> 32:47.818
and lo and behold,

32:47.870 --> 32:50.259
she had a whole string
of similar screwups

32:50.310 --> 32:51.868
going back two years.

32:51.920 --> 32:54.525
So I hired someone else
to check the ballistics.

32:54.580 --> 32:56.480
VVho?
Kurt McVeigh.

33:02.060 --> 33:04.528
God, I like watching you.

33:04.590 --> 33:06.148
Eat.

33:06.200 --> 33:08.976
Shoot

33:09.030 --> 33:10.895
Just stand.

33:10.940 --> 33:12.191
Good thing I like
being watched.

33:12.250 --> 33:14.980
[chuckles]

33:15.030 --> 33:16.076
Let's go home.

33:16.120 --> 33:19.032
[inhales sharply]
Ten more minutes.

33:19.080 --> 33:20.206
I don't want to be rude.

33:28.180 --> 33:30.603
Uh, Jason,
I need to talk to you.

33:30.660 --> 33:31.649
It's important.

33:34.440 --> 33:37.523
GIFFORD:
I did what I had to do.

33:37.580 --> 33:41.220
[panting]: I killed people
that needed killing.

33:43.410 --> 33:45.878
I know.

33:45.930 --> 33:47.056
I know, not...

33:47.110 --> 33:49.192
not you.

33:53.590 --> 33:55.899
I'm sorry.

33:55.940 --> 33:58.158
I told him to call ahead.

33:58.210 --> 34:00.075
Excuse me?

34:00.120 --> 34:02.076
I told Zach
he should call ahead,

34:02.120 --> 34:06.033
but he wanted
to surprise you.

34:06.080 --> 34:08.071
You hate me, don't you?

34:08.130 --> 34:10.121
No.

34:11.170 --> 34:12.956
We are in love.

34:13.000 --> 34:14.956
I know.

34:15.000 --> 34:17.309
We're just worried that
things are moving too fast.

34:17.350 --> 34:18.999
How long have you known
each other?

34:19.050 --> 34:20.358
A year.

34:20.400 --> 34:22.095
Do you really think that's...

34:22.140 --> 34:25.223
long enough to make the biggest
commitment of your life?

34:25.280 --> 34:28.090
How long did you know each other
before you got married?

34:28.150 --> 34:29.447
Three years.

34:29.500 --> 34:30.535
And now you're divorcing.

34:30.590 --> 34:35.152
[soft chuckle]
Yes.

34:35.200 --> 34:37.236
That's why I'm concerned.

34:37.290 --> 34:41.898
I don't want Zach, or you,

34:41.940 --> 34:43.680
to go through what I am.

34:43.730 --> 34:46.119
But that's the thing,

34:46.170 --> 34:47.159
we won't.

34:47.210 --> 34:49.030
Well, you don't know that.

34:49.080 --> 34:54.734
No, I mean we won't go
through all the... mess.

34:54.780 --> 34:57.169
It's just marriage.

34:57.220 --> 34:59.734
My parents divorced,

34:59.790 --> 35:02.179
but they still see
each other,

35:02.230 --> 35:05.358
they still love each other.

35:05.400 --> 35:09.700
But they see
other people, too.

35:09.750 --> 35:11.627
Marriage should work for us,

35:11.670 --> 35:15.197
not us for marriage.

35:15.240 --> 35:18.619
If Zach doesn't like France,
he can leave me.

35:18.680 --> 35:20.716
Come back home, go to school.

35:24.070 --> 35:28.154
If he meets someone else
he loves more, then...

35:28.210 --> 35:29.723
why should I trap him?

35:29.770 --> 35:32.944
Marriage should be fun,
it shouldn't be this...

35:33.000 --> 35:35.161
weight,

35:35.220 --> 35:37.688
this death knell.

35:37.740 --> 35:41.176
Well...

35:41.220 --> 35:44.690
if it isn't permanent,
then why get married at all?

35:44.750 --> 35:47.139
Taxes.

35:47.180 --> 35:49.398
GIFFORD:
Forgive me, Father,

35:49.450 --> 35:51.486
for I have sinned.

35:51.540 --> 35:54.759
I have hurt so many people.

35:59.500 --> 36:02.367
Peter can explain
everything.

36:02.420 --> 36:03.842
I'm sure he can.

36:03.900 --> 36:05.197
He vetoed the blood splatter

36:05.250 --> 36:07.593
because the lab tech botched
the evidence collection.

36:07.640 --> 36:10.154
Turns out she has a history
of sloppy mistakes.

36:10.210 --> 36:11.598
Why'd he sign in at the lab?

36:11.640 --> 36:13.119
He was checking up on the tech.

36:13.170 --> 36:14.421
And the missing bullets?

36:17.470 --> 36:19.290
I'm sorry,
but I have to ask, Jason,

36:19.350 --> 36:24.174
are your feelings for Alicia
getting in the way of this?

36:24.220 --> 36:26.871
If you think so,
feel free to fire me.

36:26.920 --> 36:30.617
You know, you're right.

36:30.660 --> 36:33.003
Thank you.

36:33.060 --> 36:34.869
You can send me your bill.

36:49.590 --> 36:52.548
You must have one
hell of a union.

36:52.600 --> 36:53.897
Excuse me?

36:53.950 --> 36:57.465
Botched hair evidence
in a 2011 rape trial,

36:57.510 --> 37:02.072
misidentified bite marks
in a 2010 aggravated assault,

37:02.130 --> 37:04.564
and yet you still
have a job.

37:04.610 --> 37:05.952
What do you want, Mr. Crouse?

37:06.000 --> 37:07.251
I didn't do my
homework before,

37:07.310 --> 37:09.778
but you have quite a
history of sloppy mistakes

37:09.830 --> 37:11.786
costing Peter Florrick
convictions.

37:11.830 --> 37:15.573
And you didn't tell me that
you walked through the blood

37:15.620 --> 37:17.747
at the_Richard Locke
crime scene.

37:17.800 --> 37:20.485
There were at least
a dozen cops in that apartment.

37:20.540 --> 37:23.316
There was no room
to maneuver,

37:23.370 --> 37:24.189
but I didn't lose
those bullets.

37:24.240 --> 37:25.138
Did the AUSA interview you?

37:25.190 --> 37:26.794
I'm not talking anymore.

37:26.850 --> 37:28.272
Why are you setting Florrick up?

37:28.330 --> 37:29.581
I'm not.

37:29.630 --> 37:31.234
I'm telling you the truth.

37:31.290 --> 37:32.939
No, you are lying.

37:32.980 --> 37:35.335
And you say that
up on the stand,

37:35.380 --> 37:36.722
you will be charged
with perjury.

37:36.770 --> 37:38.328
Are you threatening me?
No.

37:38.380 --> 37:40.462
I am just stating
the facts, ma'am.

37:40.510 --> 37:43.161
Next time you talk to the AUSA,

37:43.210 --> 37:45.258
I'd share that little fact.

37:47.520 --> 37:48.953
[phone ringing]

37:49.000 --> 37:51.218
[scoffs]

37:53.400 --> 37:54.389
Mr. Canning.

37:54.440 --> 37:55.953
Long time, no hear.

37:56.010 --> 37:57.227
Yes.

37:57.270 --> 37:59.226
I miss you, Alicia.

37:59.270 --> 38:00.703
How's everything going for you?

38:00.750 --> 38:02.229
Good, thank you.

38:02.280 --> 38:03.224
And you?

38:03.280 --> 38:05.271
Well, maybe you can help me.

38:05.320 --> 38:07.231
I'm representing Cary Agos,

38:07.280 --> 38:08.622
and I need to know
if Peter's gonna be loyal

38:08.670 --> 38:10.319
to his former deputy,

38:10.370 --> 38:13.100
keep him out of this
little legal mess or-or not.

38:13.160 --> 38:15.458
I have no idea,
but I will pass on the message.

38:15.510 --> 38:17.637
Maybe I should be asking if
he's gonna keep you out of it.

38:17.680 --> 38:20.205
I don't know
what you're talking about.

38:20.250 --> 38:21.638
You've had a lot of interaction

38:21.690 --> 38:23.726
with Lloyd Garber
over the years.

38:23.770 --> 38:26.330
You wrote him thank-you notes
for fund-raisers.

38:26.390 --> 38:27.209
Okay.

38:27.260 --> 38:28.420
And?

38:28.480 --> 38:29.640
You waived your
spousal privilege

38:29.690 --> 38:31.339
during the grand jury hearings,

38:31.390 --> 38:33.381
and, uh,
if the prosecutor asks you

38:33.440 --> 38:37.137
to testify about Peter's
relationship with Lloyd Garber,

38:37.180 --> 38:38.693
he could easily
turn it around on you.

38:38.750 --> 38:39.876
Good-bye, Mr. Canning.

38:39.920 --> 38:41.091
Which is why you need

38:41.140 --> 38:44.223
to think about giving Peter up.

38:47.360 --> 38:50.363
And there's the last joke.

38:50.410 --> 38:52.321
Where are you, huh?

38:52.370 --> 38:54.235
Where?

39:04.420 --> 39:05.819
Okay, this is it.
Good night.

39:05.860 --> 39:07.509
I didn't get to talk
to you all evening.

39:07.560 --> 39:12.076
Tell me why I should be a lawyer
in three words or less.

39:12.130 --> 39:13.643
You're...

39:13.690 --> 39:14.645
you're smart.

39:14.700 --> 39:18.522
Okay, I'll take that.

39:18.570 --> 39:19.525
We have to talk.

39:19.570 --> 39:20.821
I know.

39:20.880 --> 39:22.529
No, we reallyhave to talk.I know.

39:22.570 --> 39:26.006
This is in case we die tomorrow.

39:26.050 --> 39:27.790
Okay, let's not die tomorrow.

39:32.450 --> 39:33.405
See you at work.

39:33.450 --> 39:35.406
Firm of the Amazons.

39:35.460 --> 39:36.927
I like that.[chuckles]

39:36.980 --> 39:38.402
Thanks for everything.You're welcome.

39:38.460 --> 39:40.416
Maybe one day you can teach me
how to be happy.

39:40.460 --> 39:42.451
Not sure
I can teach you anything.

39:42.510 --> 39:43.499
[soft chuckle]

39:47.250 --> 39:48.205
Oh.

39:48.250 --> 39:49.945
Mm.

39:49.990 --> 39:51.207
I've been drinking.

39:51.250 --> 39:53.332
I can see that.

39:53.390 --> 39:55.608
Oh, you're such a good daughter.

39:55.650 --> 39:56.776
I love you.

39:56.820 --> 39:58.128
I love you, too.

39:58.170 --> 39:59.728
And I'm glad
you're leaving him

39:59.780 --> 40:01.509
and going with the hunk.

40:01.570 --> 40:03.526
Okay, Mom.
Thanks.

40:03.570 --> 40:04.787
I just want you to be happy.

40:04.830 --> 40:06.138
[voice breaking]:
Is that wrong?

40:06.180 --> 40:07.613
Where's Owen?
Oh, I'm here.

40:07.660 --> 40:11.130
Mm, I want you both
to be happy.

40:11.190 --> 40:12.259
You'll get her home safe?

40:12.320 --> 40:13.446
Of course.

40:13.490 --> 40:15.572
I love you.
I love you, too.

40:15.630 --> 40:17.973
And I love you both.

40:18.020 --> 40:19.976
It's the only good thing
about me.

40:20.020 --> 40:21.453
[all chuckle]I love you both.

40:24.070 --> 40:25.025
JACKIE:
Alicia.

40:25.070 --> 40:27.459
Thank you, it was beautiful.

40:27.510 --> 40:29.068
Jackie, I'm glad you're happy.

40:29.120 --> 40:31.509
But I won't be seeing you again.

40:31.550 --> 40:33.598
Why not?

40:33.640 --> 40:35.426
You're divorcing my son.

40:35.470 --> 40:38.769
And I just wanted you to know,

40:38.820 --> 40:40.811
we're more alike than not.

40:40.870 --> 40:43.088
HOWARD:
Good night and thank you.

40:43.130 --> 40:45.826
This was, by far,
the best ketubah signing

40:45.870 --> 40:47.826
I've ever been to.

40:47.880 --> 40:48.869
Good night, Howard.

40:48.920 --> 40:49.909
Good night.

40:53.620 --> 40:55.053
We're leaving, Mom.

40:55.100 --> 40:56.533
I know.

40:56.580 --> 40:58.275
["Wave of Mutilation"
by Rhett Miller playing]

40:58.320 --> 41:00.094
Text me.

41:03.590 --> 41:05.490
Be good, please.

41:05.550 --> 41:08.496
I will.

41:11.550 --> 41:13.506
Cease to resist

41:13.550 --> 41:17.850
Giving my good-byes

41:17.910 --> 41:19.593
I don't want to die!

41:19.650 --> 41:21.299
Drive my car

41:21.340 --> 41:22.295
God!

41:22.340 --> 41:23.898
Into the ocean

41:23.950 --> 41:24.951
Mother!

41:25.000 --> 41:26.126
PETER:
No, you don't understand.

41:26.170 --> 41:27.512
I'm sorry!

41:27.570 --> 41:30.562
That's not a plea bargain.

41:30.610 --> 41:32.953
No, look,
even if I were guilty,

41:33.010 --> 41:34.614
I'd fight that, okay?

41:34.660 --> 41:36.651
On a wave of mutilation

41:36.710 --> 41:37.699
[sighs]

41:37.750 --> 41:38.705
Wave

41:38.750 --> 41:40.001
Did I miss Zach?

41:40.060 --> 41:41.709
Yeah, he left.

41:41.760 --> 41:43.967
He said he'd call you tomorrow.

41:44.020 --> 41:45.408
Is he going?

41:45.450 --> 41:46.530
To France?
Yeah.

41:46.590 --> 41:48.103
Yeah.

41:48.150 --> 41:51.677
[heavy sigh]
I'll talk to him.

41:51.720 --> 41:54.029
No. Don't.

41:54.070 --> 41:57.153
It's his mistake,
let him make it.

41:57.210 --> 41:59.201
I'm sorry.

42:00.300 --> 42:01.904
You look exhausted.

42:01.950 --> 42:04.510
I'll be out of your hair
in a second.
Don't worry.

42:04.560 --> 42:06.642
All I have is a kitchen
full of dirty dishes.

42:08.650 --> 42:10.823
I've kissed mermaids

42:10.870 --> 42:12.212
I rode the El Nio

